The Olugbon of Orile Igbon, Ogbomosho, and Vice Chairman, Oyo State Council of Obas, Oba Francis Alao, has expressed confidence in the ability of the Oniru of Iru Land, Oba Omogbolahan Lawal, Abisogun II, to use his experience in governance to bring development to his kingdom. Oba Alao, who spoke in Lagos when he visited the Oniru, said he had seen the expertise shown by Oba Lawal while he was a commissioner in Lagos State, adding that the people of Iru land made a right choice in enthroning him. The Oniru thanked the Olugbon for the visit, saying he would continue to discharge his roles in his kingdom without fear or favour.